So, good news is that I have a very loyal team.  I had to share that I haven’t been sleeping well at all, up tossing and turning all night worrying about all of this.  I had to make sure they knew to ignore any middle of the night emails/texts from me.  Bad news, and I do not think it is material, is that at least one person now thinks I am have lost it, but they are so loyal that they are still with me.  

At about 11 last night, I sent my entire leadership team text messages, telling them that I was sorry, the war had changed, and the rules were different now.  I let them know that they needed to do whatever they thought was best to win and if they get negative feedback, even from me, ignore it.  I told my team, they are at war, there are casualties in war, and **reality is a construct, so construct whatever reality they needed to to maximize our success.**  I let them know that I was going to stop using redlines and they should too.  I hate redlines, but I use them because I thought it was a common courtesy.  I finished up with letting them know that I fully support them, no matter what they decide to do…

The one person that concerns me is [Redacted], but I will try to reel him back in next week.  I love these guys.  But, like you, they are still getting up to speed on my style.  I think [Redacted] may not have shared the entire 2014 Princeton Commencement Speech.
